{
  "texts": [
    "When b = 1, the judge prefers the first response y 1; otherwise it prefers the second response y 2.",
    "We consider pairwise comparisons to simplify exposition and discuss an extension to multiple responses in Section D.1.",
    "This work is motivated by the observation that the scores of pre-trained LLM judges (Section 3) are not calibrated to any given domain, simply because they are trained on general world knowledge.",
    "To obtain better scores, we learn to predict them from rationales of existing judges and human scores in the domain.",
    "Our predictors are generalized linear models (GLMs) (Wolke and Schwetlick, 1988), which generalize linear models to non-linear functions while inheriting their efficiency."
  ]
}